git-jira

Simple, yet useful git command to set current JIRA ticket you are working on.

Saves time - set once, and it will auto-append JIRA ticket code to your commit messages.


Intallation:
    Put it anywhere so it is visible in your $PATH.


Usage:
    git jira [-arg1, --arg2...]
        commit with current JIRA ticket code. Args are passed to 'git commit'.
    git jira set [CODE]
        set current JIRA ticket to 'CODE', if specified, or clean existing one.
    git jira show
        show current JIRA ticket code.
    git jira file
        show the file path where the ticket code is stored.
